16-692.Water commissioner; city council member and mayor ineligible.

No member of the city council or the mayor of a city of the first class shall be eligible to the office of water commissioner during the term for which he or she shall be elected.

SourceLaws 1901, c. 18, § 64, p. 278;R.S.1913, § 4964;C.S.1922, § 4133;C.S.1929, § 16-662;R.S.1943, § 16-692;Laws 2016, LB704, § 151;Laws 2019, LB194, § 71.
